<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Jamie Murray and Neal Skupski's US Open run ended with a quarter-final loss to Bruno Soares and Mate Pavic in the men's doubles.</p>

<p>Murray won the title with Soares four years ago but it was the Brazilian who had the last laugh here in a 6-2 7-6 (4) victory.</p>

<p>Murray and Skupski made a poor start, losing the first four games, but matched their opponents in the second set and had three set points at 5-4 before going down in the tie-break.</p>

<p>Jamie Murray and Neal Skupski's US Open run ended with a quarter-final loss</p>

<p>The pair's loss leaves Joe Salisbury, playing with American Rajeev Ram, as the only British player left in the tournament.</p>

<p>The Australian Open champions face eighth seeds Wesley Koolhof and Nikola Mektic in the semi-finals.</p>
